column5: I took today off so I could stay out late last night and it paid off. I hit two spots and got 5 fish in total (65cm, 55cm, 53cm, 45cm and 41cm).  Night pics are never great on an iPhone but here's a picture of the big girl. She weighed in at 5.4 pounds.    Fish were caught on bobber and minnow or Pickerel rig/drop shot. It was a nice night out but that wind was something else. I'll be out again Saturday. Good luck!
Nice to hear about a successful fishing expedition! Thanks for sharing.
Nice! that wind is hitting us now!
That a beauty! Nice job and thanks for showing us! HH
they are on the run indeed...my report is pending as well...the size is coming...man i cant wait till february when the big spawners are in.  nice fish!
Thanks guys, I can't wait to get back out there tomorrow....

Thanks guys, I can't wait to get back out there tomorrow....  lucky guy, i just did 9 days straight and guess where im really sad im not gonna be tomorrow...fishing...  i am getting my second sitting of a fishing tattoo done though...so thats something lol
Nice fish bud!  My kiddos got a hockey tourny right now so im sneaking out inbetween games to see if the bigger eyes are on.  Good luck out there today!
Nice fishes buddy, good night out in my booksâ€¦.looking forward to saturday's pics.
Uh oh - now the pressure is on to produce ?
Hahahah. So true.  I hope ya get em saturday man! Im just taking a quick break but im seriously striking out today??? an hour in and not one bite...
Nice fish for sure. i have been trying to go Crappie fishing the last few days to see if they have balled up yet for winter.   Art
So falleye finally showed up...nice fish man.
Thanks. It sure took long enough though! I think I've been out a dozen times in the last 4-5 weeks.  No, I am not complaining about fishing too much lol!
Some very nice numbers there!  If the wind isn't too bad I'll be giving it a try from shore tomorrow at my folks place
Nice! You guys posting these pics are killing me hahaha!  Thanks for sharing!
I guess "Dutch" is European...  Measures in centimeters.  That could be a first here.  Great fishing regardless.
Measures in centimeters.  That could be a first here. I always do too as zone 17 is 35 to 50 cm keepers on most lakes.  Balsam is the one exception
I need to do some exploring around home here for a good shore walleye spot .  Looks like a blast.
Nice haul Dutch!  The super moon is Monday night, I bet that would be a good night to be out there and wrap up the season.

Thanks Chris. I'm expecting it to be busy at "the spot" tonight. I also took off Wednesday so I can spend Tuesday night there. I'm think I might try going Monday after work if I can too. Time to make hay while the Sun is shining. Then I have to find something else to catch while I wait for ice....
